COOK chicken in a large Dutch oven in boiling water to cover 45 minutes or until done. REMOVE chicken from broth, reserving broth for another use. Cool chicken. Skin, bone, and chop chicken. SAUTE onion and bell pepper in hot oil in Dutch oven until tender. Add chicken, tomato, and next 4 ingredients. COMBINE flour and 1 cup water, whisking until smooth. Stir into chicken mixture. Add potato and next 5 ingredients. COVER and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 20 to 30 minutes. Add corn and lima beans, and cook 10 minutes.